  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ARCCII Recovery, Reconciliation and Resilience: Humanitarian Assistance for Conflict-Affected Households of in Areas of Protracted Conflict and High Returns</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Based in South Masisi, the program is in recognition of the cyclical nature of displacement in the zone and the need to increase the capacity of conflict affected households to deal with the regular shocks affecting their livelihoods. 
While some areas of Masisi Territory continue to suffer from conflict between armed groups and have greater accessible issues (requiring humanitarian funding), other areas have witnessed significant returns and are fragile but remain calm. This program proposes to work in this latter area, where the focus is on building resilience to crisis for poor households. This is done through cash transfer,  voucher support for households in addition to further analysis of the question of coping mechanisms. 
In conjunction with Solidarities and Mercy Corp who are implementing the ARCCII under UNICEF, this program will seek to collate and disseminate learning on the relative effectiveness of these different approaches.</narrative>
  </description>
